## Shift & Availability Array Format
Both job.shift_patterns and candidate.availability use plain English strings.
Standard values:
'Early (6am-2pm)', 'Late (2pm-10pm)', 'Nights (10pm-6am)',
'Days (7am-7pm)', 'Nights (7pm-7am)', '4-on 4-off',
'Mornings', 'Afternoons', 'Weekends', 'Flexible'
Matching is case-insensitive exact string comparison.

---

## RLS Policies (current)
- applications: 
  Candidates INSERT (job must be active)
  Candidates SELECT own (via candidate_id → candidates.user_id)
  Recruiters ALL (scoped to their jobs via recruiter_id)
- candidates: 
  Anyone INSERT (with_check: true)
  Candidates SELECT/UPDATE own (user_id = auth.uid())
- employers: Recruiters ALL (scoped to created_by)
- jobs: Recruiters ALL (scoped to recruiter_id)
- recruiter_employers: Users SELECT own, Service role ALL

---

## Key Architecture Decisions
- Auth: Magic Links only. No passwords. Ever.
- Registration flow:
  1. Register page collects name/email/postcode
  2. Stores in localStorage as 'hirefast_pending_candidate'
  3. Sends magic link via supabase.auth.signInWithOtp()
  4. MagicLinkHandler creates candidates row after session established
  5. Redirects to /candidate/verify
- Post-auth routing: MagicLinkHandler checks recruiter_employers.
  Match found → /recruiter/applicants
  No match + existing candidate → /candidate/jobs
  No match + new candidate → /candidate/verify
- Recruiter layout: RecruiterLayout.tsx wraps all recruiter pages.
  max-w-5xl canvas. src/layouts/RecruiterLayout.tsx
- Candidate nav: HireFast wordmark left + Jobs/Settings links right
- Commute scoring: Postcodes.io (free, no API key)
  Postcode must be stripped of spaces before API call:
  postcode.replace(/\s+/g, '')
  Haversine distance. Journey time by transport mode.
  Utility: src/lib/commuteScoring.ts
  Add 200ms delay between calls to avoid rate limiting
- Match scoring: 50% location + 50% skills
  Location: low=100, medium=60, high=20
  Skills: matched/required * 100. No required skills = 100
  Fires async after application INSERT — never blocks success screen
- Candidate sheet: Clicking row in ManageApplicants opens
  Shadcn Sheet (side="right", max-w-2xl). Never navigate away.
- Postcode privacy: show outward code only (e.g. "S1")
  Never log or display full postcodes
- Self-declared data: RTW, NI, DBS always labelled "(Self-declared)"
- Duplicate applications: UNIQUE constraint on (job_id, email)
  Handle 409 as success if application already exists

